770  template<typename T, typename... Args>
771  static T *create(Args &&... args) {
772  AllocatorType<T> alloc;
773  auto deleter = [&](T *object) {
774  alloc.deallocate(object, 1);
775  };
776  std::unique_ptr<T, decltype(deleter)> object(alloc.allocate(1), deleter);
777  alloc.construct(object.get(), std::forward<Args>(args)...);
778  return object.release();
779  }

1571  basic_json(std::initializer_list<basic_json> init,
1572  bool type_deduction = true,
1573  value_t manual_type = value_t::array) {
1574  // the initializer list could describe an object
1575  bool is_an_object = true;
1576 
1577  // check if each element is an array with two elements whose first
1578  // element is a string
1579  for (const auto &element : init) {
1580  if (not element.is_array() or element.size() != 2
1581  or not element[0].is_string()) {
1582  // we found an element that makes it impossible to use the
1583  // initializer list as object
1584  is_an_object = false;
1585  break;
1586  }
1587  }
1588 
1589  // adjust type if type deduction is not wanted
1590  if (not type_deduction) {
1591  // if array is wanted, do not create an object though possible
1592  if (manual_type == value_t::array) {
1593  is_an_object = false;
1594  }
1595 
1596  // if object is wanted but impossible, throw an exception
1597  if (manual_type == value_t::object and not is_an_object) {
1598  throw std::domain_error("cannot create object from initializer list");
1599  }
1600  }
1601 
1602  if (is_an_object) {
1603  // the initializer list is a list of pairs -> create object
1604  m_type = value_t::object;
1605  m_value = value_t::object;
1606 
1607  assert(m_value.object != nullptr);
1608 
1609  for (auto &element : init) {
1610  m_value.object->emplace(*(element[0].m_value.string), element[1]);
1611  }
1612  }
1613  else {
1614  // the initializer list describes an array -> create array
1615  m_type = value_t::array;
1616  m_value.array = create<array_t>(init);
1617  }
1618  }

1755  template<class InputIT, typename
1756  std::enable_if<
1757  std::is_same<InputIT, typename basic_json_t::iterator>::value or
1758  std::is_same<InputIT, typename basic_json_t::const_iterator>::value, int>::type
1759  = 0>
1760  basic_json(InputIT first, InputIT last) : m_type(first.m_object->m_type) {
1761  // make sure iterator fits the current value
1762  if (first.m_object != last.m_object) {
1763  throw std::domain_error("iterators are not compatible");
1764  }
1765 
1766  // check if iterator range is complete for primitive values
1767  switch (m_type) {
1768  case value_t::boolean:
1769  case value_t::number_float:
1770  case value_t::number_integer:
1771  case value_t::number_unsigned:
1772  case value_t::string: {
1773  if (not first.m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin() or not last.m_it.primitive_iterator.is_end()) {
1774  throw std::out_of_range("iterators out of range");
1775  }
1776  break;
1777  }
1778 
1779  default: {
1780  break;

4950  3, // object
4951  4, // array

4955  2, // unsigned

5487  static std::size_t extra_space(const string_t &s) noexcept {
5488  std::size_t result = 0;
5489 
5490  for (const auto &c : s) {
5491  switch (c) {
5492  case '"':
5493  case '\\':
5494  case '\b':
5495  case '\f':
5496  case '\n':
5497  case '\r':
5498  case '\t': {
5499  // from c (1 byte) to \x (2 bytes)
5500  result += 1;
5501  break;
5502  }
5503 
5504  default: {
5505  if (c >= 0x00 and c <= 0x1f) {
5506  // from c (1 byte) to \uxxxx (6 bytes)
5507  result += 5;
5508  }
5509  break;
5510  }
5511  }
5512  }
5513 
5514  return result;
5515  }
5516 
5530  static string_t escape_string(const string_t &s) {
5531  const auto space = extra_space(s);
5532  if (space == 0) {
5533  return s;
5534  }
5535 
5536  // create a result string of necessary size
5537  string_t result(s.size() + space, '\\');
5538  std::size_t pos = 0;
5539 
5540  for (const auto &c : s) {
5541  switch (c) {
5542  // quotation mark (0x22)
5543  case '"': {
5544  result[pos + 1] = '"';
5545  pos += 2;
5546  break;
5547  }
5548 
5549  // reverse solidus (0x5c)
5550  case '\\': {
5551  // nothing to change
5552  pos += 2;
5553  break;
5554  }
5555 
5556  // backspace (0x08)
5557  case '\b': {
5558  result[pos + 1] = 'b';
5559  pos += 2;
5560  break;
5561  }
5562 
5563  // formfeed (0x0c)
5564  case '\f': {
5565  result[pos + 1] = 'f';
5566  pos += 2;
5567  break;
5568  }
5569 
5570  // newline (0x0a)
5571  case '\n': {
5572  result[pos + 1] = 'n';
5573  pos += 2;
5574  break;
5575  }
5576 
5577  // carriage return (0x0d)
5578  case '\r': {
5579  result[pos + 1] = 'r';
5580  pos += 2;
5581  break;
5582  }
5583 
5584  // horizontal tab (0x09)
5585  case '\t': {
5586  result[pos + 1] = 't';
5587  pos += 2;
5588  break;
5589  }
5590 
5591  default: {
5592  if (c >= 0x00 and c <= 0x1f) {
5593  // convert a number 0..15 to its hex representation
5594  // (0..f)
5595  const auto hexify = [](const int v) -> char {
5596  return (v < 10)
5597  ? ('0' + static_cast<char>(v))
5598  : ('a' + static_cast<char>((v - 10) & 0x1f));
5599  };
5600 
5601  // print character c as \uxxxx
5602  for (const char m :
5603  {'u', '0', '0', hexify(c >> 4), hexify(c & 0x0f)
5604  }) {
5605  result[++pos] = m;
5606  }
5607 
5608  ++pos;
5609  }
5610  else {
5611  // all other characters are added as-is
5612  result[pos++] = c;
5613  }
5614  break;
5615  }
5616  }
5617  }
5618 
5619  return result;
5620  }

5639  void dump(std::ostream &o,
5640  const bool pretty_print,
5641  const unsigned int indent_step,
5642  const unsigned int current_indent = 0) const {
5643  // variable to hold indentation for recursive calls
5644  unsigned int new_indent = current_indent;
5645 
5646  switch (m_type) {
5647  case value_t::object: {
5648  assert(m_value.object != nullptr);
5649 
5650  if (m_value.object->empty()) {
5651  o << "{}";
5652  return;
5653  }
5654 
5655  o << "{";
5656 
5657  // increase indentation
5658  if (pretty_print) {
5659  new_indent += indent_step;
5660  o << "\n";
5661  }
5662 
5663  for (auto i = m_value.object->cbegin(); i != m_value.object->cend(); ++i) {
5664  if (i != m_value.object->cbegin()) {
5665  o << (pretty_print ? ",\n" : ",");
5666  }
5667  o << string_t(new_indent, ' ') << "\""
5668  << escape_string(i->first) << "\":"
5669  << (pretty_print ? " " : "");
5670  i->second.dump(o, pretty_print, indent_step, new_indent);
5671  }
5672 
5673  // decrease indentation
5674  if (pretty_print) {
5675  new_indent -= indent_step;
5676  o << "\n";
5677  }
5678 
5679  o << string_t(new_indent, ' ') + "}";
5680  return;
5681  }
5682 
5683  case value_t::array: {
5684  assert(m_value.array != nullptr);
5685 
5686  if (m_value.array->empty()) {
5687  o << "[]";
5688  return;
5689  }
5690 
5691  o << "[";
5692 
5693  // increase indentation
5694  if (pretty_print) {
5695  new_indent += indent_step;
5696  o << "\n";
5697  }
5698 
5699  for (auto i = m_value.array->cbegin(); i != m_value.array->cend(); ++i) {
5700  if (i != m_value.array->cbegin()) {
5701  o << (pretty_print ? ",\n" : ",");
5702  }
5703  o << string_t(new_indent, ' ');
5704  i->dump(o, pretty_print, indent_step, new_indent);
5705  }
5706 
5707  // decrease indentation
5708  if (pretty_print) {
5709  new_indent -= indent_step;
5710  o << "\n";
5711  }
5712 
5713  o << string_t(new_indent, ' ') << "]";
5714  return;
5715  }
5716 
5717  case value_t::string: {
5718  assert(m_value.string != nullptr);
5719  o << string_t("\"") << escape_string(*m_value.string) << "\"";
5720  return;
5721  }
5722 
5723  case value_t::boolean: {
5724  o << (m_value.boolean ? "true" : "false");
5725  return;
5726  }
5727 
5728  case value_t::number_integer: {
5729  o << m_value.number_integer;
5730  return;
5731  }
5732 
5733  case value_t::number_unsigned: {
5734  o << m_value.number_unsigned;
5735  return;
5736  }
5737 
5738  case value_t::number_float: {
5739  // check if number was parsed from a string
5740  if (m_type.bits.parsed) {
5741  // check if parsed number had an exponent given
5742  if (m_type.bits.has_exp) {
5743  // buffer size: precision (2^8-1 = 255) + other ('-.e-xxx' = 7) + null (1)
5744  char buf[263];
5745  int len;
5746 
5747  // handle capitalization of the exponent
5748  if (m_type.bits.exp_cap) {
5749  len = snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%.*E",
5750  m_type.bits.precision, m_value.number_float) + 1;
5751  }
5752  else {
5753  len = snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%.*e",
5754  m_type.bits.precision, m_value.number_float) + 1;
5755  }
5756 
5757  // remove '+' sign from the exponent if necessary
5758  if (not m_type.bits.exp_plus) {
5759  if (len > static_cast<int>(sizeof(buf))) {
5760  len = sizeof(buf);
5761  }
5762  for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
5763  if (buf[i] == '+') {
5764  for (; i + 1 < len; i++) {
5765  buf[i] = buf[i + 1];
5766  }
5767  }
5768  }
5769  }
5770 
5771  o << buf;
5772  }
5773  else {
5774  // no exponent - output as a decimal
5775  std::stringstream ss;
5776  ss.imbue(std::locale(std::locale(), new DecimalSeparator)); // fix locale problems
5777  ss << std::setprecision(m_type.bits.precision)
5778  << std::fixed << m_value.number_float;
5779  o << ss.str();
5780  }
5781  }
5782  else {
5783  if (m_value.number_float == 0) {
5784  // special case for zero to get "0.0"/"-0.0"
5785  o << (std::signbit(m_value.number_float) ? "-0.0" : "0.0");
5786  }
5787  else {
5788  // Otherwise 6, 15 or 16 digits of precision allows
5789  // round-trip IEEE 754 string->float->string,
5790  // string->double->string or string->long
5791  // double->string; to be safe, we read this value from
5792  // std::numeric_limits<number_float_t>::digits10
5793  std::stringstream ss;
5794  ss.imbue(std::locale(std::locale(), new DecimalSeparator)); // fix locale problems
5795  ss << std::setprecision(std::numeric_limits<double>::digits10)
5796  << m_value.number_float;
5797  o << ss.str();
5798  }
5799  }
5800  return;
5801  }
5802 
5803  case value_t::discarded: {
5804  o << "<discarded>";
5805  return;
5806  }
5807 
5808  case value_t::null: {
5809  o << "null";
5810  return;
5811  }
5812  }
5813  }

6730  static string_t to_unicode(const std::size_t codepoint1,
6731  const std::size_t codepoint2 = 0) {
6732  // calculate the codepoint from the given code points
6733  std::size_t codepoint = codepoint1;
6734 
6735  // check if codepoint1 is a high surrogate
6736  if (codepoint1 >= 0xD800 and codepoint1 <= 0xDBFF) {
6737  // check if codepoint2 is a low surrogate
6738  if (codepoint2 >= 0xDC00 and codepoint2 <= 0xDFFF) {
6739  codepoint =
6740  // high surrogate occupies the most significant 22 bits
6741  (codepoint1 << 10)
6742  // low surrogate occupies the least significant 15 bits
6743  + codepoint2
6744  // there is still the 0xD800, 0xDC00 and 0x10000 noise
6745  // in the result so we have to subtract with:
6746  // (0xD800 << 10) + DC00 - 0x10000 = 0x35FDC00
6747  - 0x35FDC00;
6748  }
6749  else {
6750  throw std::invalid_argument("missing or wrong low surrogate");
6751  }
6752  }
6753 
6754  string_t result;
6755 
6756  if (codepoint < 0x80) {
6757  // 1-byte characters: 0xxxxxxx (ASCII)
6758  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(codepoint));
6759  }
6760  else if (codepoint <= 0x7ff) {
6761  // 2-byte characters: 110xxxxx 10xxxxxx
6762  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0xC0 | ((codepoint >> 6) & 0x1F)));
6763  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F)));
6764  }
6765  else if (codepoint <= 0xffff) {
6766  // 3-byte characters: 1110xxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
6767  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0xE0 | ((codepoint >> 12) & 0x0F)));
6768  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 6) & 0x3F)));
6769  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F)));
6770  }
6771  else if (codepoint <= 0x10ffff) {
6772  // 4-byte characters: 11110xxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
6773  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0xF0 | ((codepoint >> 18) & 0x07)));
6774  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 12) & 0x3F)));
6775  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 6) & 0x3F)));
6776  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F)));
6777  }
6778  else {
6779  throw std::out_of_range("code points above 0x10FFFF are invalid");
6780  }
6781 
6782  return result;
6783  }

7458  void yyfill() noexcept {
7459  if (m_stream == nullptr or not *m_stream) {
7460  return;
7461  }
7462 
7463  const auto offset_start = m_start - m_content;
7464  const auto offset_marker = m_marker - m_start;
7465  const auto offset_cursor = m_cursor - m_start;
7466 
7467  m_buffer.erase(0, static_cast<size_t>(offset_start));
7468  std::string line;
7469  assert(m_stream != nullptr);
7470  std::getline(*m_stream, line);
7471  m_buffer += "\n" + line; // add line with newline symbol
7472 
7473  m_content = reinterpret_cast<const lexer_char_t *>(m_buffer.c_str());
7474  assert(m_content != nullptr);
7475  m_start = m_content;
7476  m_marker = m_start + offset_marker;
7477  m_cursor = m_start + offset_cursor;
7478  m_limit = m_start + m_buffer.size() - 1;
7479  }

7482  string_t get_token() const {
7483  assert(m_start != nullptr);
7484  return string_t(reinterpret_cast<typename string_t::const_pointer>(m_start),
7485  static_cast<size_t>(m_cursor - m_start));
7486  }
7487 
7510  string_t get_string() const {
7511  string_t result;
7512  result.reserve(static_cast<size_t>(m_cursor - m_start - 2));
7513 
7514  // iterate the result between the quotes
7515  for (const lexer_char_t *i = m_start + 1; i < m_cursor - 1; ++i) {
7516  // process escaped characters
7517  if (*i == '\\') {
7518  // read next character
7519  ++i;
7520 
7521  switch (*i) {
7522  // the default escapes
7523  case 't': {
7524  result += "\t";
7525  break;
7526  }
7527  case 'b': {
7528  result += "\b";
7529  break;
7530  }
7531  case 'f': {
7532  result += "\f";
7533  break;
7534  }
7535  case 'n': {
7536  result += "\n";
7537  break;
7538  }
7539  case 'r': {
7540  result += "\r";
7541  break;
7542  }
7543  case '\\': {
7544  result += "\\";
7545  break;
7546  }
7547  case '/': {
7548  result += "/";
7549  break;
7550  }
7551  case '"': {
7552  result += "\"";
7553  break;
7554  }
7555 
7556  // unicode
7557  case 'u': {
7558  // get code xxxx from uxxxx
7559  auto codepoint =
7560  std::strtoul(std::string(reinterpret_cast<typename string_t::const_pointer>(i + 1),
7561  4).c_str(), nullptr, 16);
7562 
7563  // check if codepoint is a high surrogate
7564  if (codepoint >= 0xD800 and codepoint <= 0xDBFF) {
7565  // make sure there is a subsequent unicode
7566  if ((i + 6 >= m_limit) or *(i + 5) != '\\' or *(i + 6) != 'u') {
7567  throw std::invalid_argument("missing low surrogate");
7568  }
7569 
7570  // get code yyyy from uxxxx\uyyyy
7571  auto codepoint2 =
7572  std::strtoul(std::string(reinterpret_cast<typename string_t::const_pointer>
7573  (i + 7), 4).c_str(), nullptr, 16);
7574  result += to_unicode(codepoint, codepoint2);
7575  // skip the next 10 characters (xxxx\uyyyy)
7576  i += 10;
7577  }
7578  else {
7579  // add unicode character(s)
7580  result += to_unicode(codepoint);
7581  // skip the next four characters (xxxx)
7582  i += 4;
7583  }
7584  break;
7585  }
7586  }
7587  }
7588  else {
7589  // all other characters are just copied to the end of the
7590  // string
7591  result.append(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(*i));
7592  }
7593  }
7594 
7595  return result;
7596  }

7687  void get_number(basic_json &result) const {
7688  assert(m_start != nullptr);
7689 
7690  const lexer::lexer_char_t *curptr = m_start;
7691 
7692  // remember this number was parsed (for later serialization)
7693  result.m_type.bits.parsed = true;
7694 
7695  // 'found_radix_point' will be set to 0xFF upon finding a radix
7696  // point and later used to mask in/out the precision depending
7697  // whether a radix is found i.e. 'precision &= found_radix_point'
7698  uint8_t found_radix_point = 0;
7699  uint8_t precision = 0;
7700 
7701  // accumulate the integer conversion result (unsigned for now)
7702  number_unsigned_t value = 0;
7703 
7704  // maximum absolute value of the relevant integer type
7705  number_unsigned_t max;
7706 
7707  // temporarily store the type to avoid unecessary bitfield access
7708  value_t type;
7709 
7710  // look for sign
7711  if (*curptr == '-') {
7712  type = value_t::number_integer;
7713  max = static_cast<uint64_t>(std::numeric_limits<number_integer_t>::max()) + 1;
7714  curptr++;
7715  }
7716  else {
7717  type = value_t::number_unsigned;
7718  max = static_cast<uint64_t>(std::numeric_limits<number_unsigned_t>::max());
7719  }
7720 
7721  // count the significant figures
7722  for (; curptr < m_cursor; curptr++) {
7723  // quickly skip tests if a digit
7724  if (*curptr < '0' || *curptr > '9') {
7725  if (*curptr == '.') {
7726  // don't count '.' but change to float
7727  type = value_t::number_float;
7728 
7729  // reset precision count
7730  precision = 0;
7731  found_radix_point = 0xFF;
7732  continue;
7733  }
7734  // assume exponent (if not then will fail parse): change to
7735  // float, stop counting and record exponent details
7736  type = value_t::number_float;
7737  result.m_type.bits.has_exp = true;
7738 
7739  // exponent capitalization
7740  result.m_type.bits.exp_cap = (*curptr == 'E');
7741 
7742  // exponent '+' sign
7743  result.m_type.bits.exp_plus = (*(++curptr) == '+');
7744  break;
7745  }
7746 
7747  // skip if definitely not an integer
7748  if (type != value_t::number_float) {
7749  // multiply last value by ten and add the new digit
7750  auto temp = value * 10 + *curptr - 0x30;
7751 
7752  // test for overflow
7753  if (temp < value || temp > max) {
7754  // overflow
7755  type = value_t::number_float;
7756  }
7757  else {
7758  // no overflow - save it
7759  value = temp;
7760  }
7761  }
7762  ++precision;
7763  }
7764 
7765  // If no radix point was found then precision would now be set to
7766  // the number of digits, which is wrong - clear it.
7767  result.m_type.bits.precision = precision & found_radix_point;
7768 
7769  // save the value (if not a float)
7770  if (type == value_t::number_unsigned) {
7771  result.m_value.number_unsigned = value;
7772  }
7773  else if (type == value_t::number_integer) {
7774  result.m_value.number_integer = -static_cast<number_integer_t>(value);
7775  }
7776  else {
7777  // parse with strtod
7778  result.m_value.number_float = str_to_float_t(static_cast<number_float_t *>(nullptr), NULL);
7779  }
7780 
7781  // save the type
7782  result.m_type = type;
7783  }
7784 
7785  private:
7787  std::istream *m_stream = nullptr;
7789  string_t m_buffer;
7791  const lexer_char_t *m_content = nullptr;
7793  const lexer_char_t *m_start = nullptr;
7795  const lexer_char_t *m_marker = nullptr;
7797  const lexer_char_t *m_cursor = nullptr;
7799  const lexer_char_t *m_limit = nullptr;
7800  };

7807  class parser {
7808  public:
7810  parser(const string_t &s, parser_callback_t cb = nullptr) noexcept
7811  : callback(cb), m_lexer(s) {
7812  // read first token
7813  get_token();
7814  }
7815 
7817  parser(std::istream &_is, parser_callback_t cb = nullptr) noexcept
7818  : callback(cb), m_lexer(&_is) {
7819  // read first token
7820  get_token();
7821  }
7822 
7824  basic_json parse() {
7825  basic_json result = parse_internal(true);
7826 
7827  expect(lexer::token_type::end_of_input);
7828 
7829  // return parser result and replace it with null in case the
7830  // top-level value was discarded by the callback function
7831  return result.is_discarded() ? basic_json() : result;
7832  }
7833 
7834  private:
7836  basic_json parse_internal(bool keep) {
7837  auto result = basic_json(value_t::discarded);
7838 
7839  switch (last_token) {
7840  case lexer::token_type::begin_object: {
7841  if (keep and (not callback or (keep = callback(depth++, parse_event_t::object_start, result)))) {
7842  // explicitly set result to object to cope with {}
7843  result.m_type = value_t::object;
7844  result.m_value = json_value(value_t::object);
7845  }
7846 
7847  // read next token
7848  get_token();
7849 
7850  // closing } -> we are done
7851  if (last_token == lexer::token_type::end_object) {
7852  get_token();
7853  if (keep and callback and not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::object_end, result)) {
7854  result = basic_json(value_t::discarded);
7855  }
7856  return result;
7857  }
7858 
7859  // no comma is expected here
7860  unexpect(lexer::token_type::value_separator);
7861 
7862  // otherwise: parse key-value pairs
7863  do {
7864  // ugly, but could be fixed with loop reorganization
7865  if (last_token == lexer::token_type::value_separator) {
7866  get_token();
7867  }
7868 
7869  // store key
7870  expect(lexer::token_type::value_string);
7871  const auto key = m_lexer.get_string();
7872 
7873  bool keep_tag = false;
7874  if (keep) {
7875  if (callback) {
7876  basic_json k(key);
7877  keep_tag = callback(depth, parse_event_t::key, k);
7878  }
7879  else {
7880  keep_tag = true;
7881  }
7882  }
7883 
7884  // parse separator (:)
7885  get_token();
7886  expect(lexer::token_type::name_separator);
7887 
7888  // parse and add value
7889  get_token();
7890  auto value = parse_internal(keep);
7891  if (keep and keep_tag and not value.is_discarded()) {
7892  result[key] = std::move(value);
7893  }
7894  }
7895  while (last_token == lexer::token_type::value_separator);
7896 
7897  // closing }
7898  expect(lexer::token_type::end_object);
7899  get_token();
7900  if (keep and callback and not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::object_end, result)) {
7901  result = basic_json(value_t::discarded);
7902  }
7903 
7904  return result;
7905  }
7906 
7907  case lexer::token_type::begin_array: {
7908  if (keep and (not callback or (keep = callback(depth++, parse_event_t::array_start, result)))) {
7909  // explicitly set result to object to cope with []
7910  result.m_type = value_t::array;
7911  result.m_value = json_value(value_t::array);
7912  }
7913 
7914  // read next token
7915  get_token();
7916 
7917  // closing ] -> we are done
7918  if (last_token == lexer::token_type::end_array) {
7919  get_token();
7920  if (callback and not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::array_end, result)) {
7921  result = basic_json(value_t::discarded);
7922  }
7923  return result;
7924  }
7925 
7926  // no comma is expected here
7927  unexpect(lexer::token_type::value_separator);
7928 
7929  // otherwise: parse values
7930  do {
7931  // ugly, but could be fixed with loop reorganization
7932  if (last_token == lexer::token_type::value_separator) {
7933  get_token();
7934  }
7935 
7936  // parse value
7937  auto value = parse_internal(keep);
7938  if (keep and not value.is_discarded()) {
7939  result.push_back(std::move(value));
7940  }
7941  }
7942  while (last_token == lexer::token_type::value_separator);
7943 
7944  // closing ]
7945  expect(lexer::token_type::end_array);
7946  get_token();
7947  if (keep and callback and not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::array_end, result)) {
7948  result = basic_json(value_t::discarded);
7949  }
7950 
7951  return result;
7952  }
7953 
7954  case lexer::token_type::literal_null: {
7955  get_token();
7956  result.m_type = value_t::null;
7957  break;
7958  }
7959 
7960  case lexer::token_type::value_string: {
7961  const auto s = m_lexer.get_string();
7962  get_token();
7963  result = basic_json(s);
7964  break;
7965  }
7966 
7967  case lexer::token_type::literal_true: {
7968  get_token();
7969  result.m_type = value_t::boolean;
7970  result.m_value = true;
7971  break;
7972  }
7973 
7974  case lexer::token_type::literal_false: {
7975  get_token();
7976  result.m_type = value_t::boolean;
7977  result.m_value = false;
7978  break;
7979  }
7980 
7981  case lexer::token_type::value_number: {
7982  m_lexer.get_number(result);
7983  get_token();
7984  break;
7985  }
7986 
7987  default: {
7988  // the last token was unexpected
7989  unexpect(last_token);
7990  }
7991  }
7992 
7993  if (keep and callback and not callback(depth, parse_event_t::value, result)) {
7994  result = basic_json(value_t::discarded);
7995  }
7996  return result;
7997  }
7998 
8000  typename lexer::token_type get_token() noexcept {
8001  last_token = m_lexer.scan();
8002  return last_token;
8003  }
8004 
8005  void expect(typename lexer::token_type t) const {
8006  if (t != last_token) {
8007  std::string error_msg = "parse error - unexpected ";
8008  error_msg += (last_token == lexer::token_type::parse_error ? ("'" + m_lexer.get_token() + "'") :
8009  lexer::token_type_name(last_token));
8010  error_msg += "; expected " + lexer::token_type_name(t);
8011  throw std::invalid_argument(error_msg);
8012  }
8013  }
8014 
8015  void unexpect(typename lexer::token_type t) const {
8016  if (t == last_token) {
8017  std::string error_msg = "parse error - unexpected ";
8018  error_msg += (last_token == lexer::token_type::parse_error ? ("'" + m_lexer.get_token() + "'") :
8019  lexer::token_type_name(last_token));
8020  throw std::invalid_argument(error_msg);
8021  }
8022  }
8023 
8024  private:
8026  int depth = 0;
8028  parser_callback_t callback;
8030  typename lexer::token_type last_token = lexer::token_type::uninitialized;
8032  lexer m_lexer;
8033  };

8137  reference get_and_create(reference j) const {
8138  pointer result = &j;
8139 
8140  // in case no reference tokens exist, return a reference to the
8141  // JSON value j which will be overwritten by a primitive value
8142  for (const auto &reference_token : reference_tokens) {
8143  switch (result->m_type) {
8144  case value_t::null: {
8145  if (reference_token == "0") {
8146  // start a new array if reference token is 0
8147  result = &result->operator[](0);
8148  }
8149  else {
8150  // start a new object otherwise
8151  result = &result->operator[](reference_token);
8152  }
8153  break;
8154  }
8155 
8156  case value_t::object: {
8157  // create an entry in the object
8158  result = &result->operator[](reference_token);
8159  break;
8160  }
8161 
8162  case value_t::array: {
8163  // create an entry in the array
8164  result = &result->operator[](static_cast<size_type>(std::stoi(reference_token)));
8165  break;
8166  }
8167 
8168  /*
8169  The following code is only reached if there exists a
8170  reference token _and_ the current value is primitive. In
8171  this case, we have an error situation, because primitive
8172  values may only occur as single value; that is, with an
8173  empty list of reference tokens.
8174  */
8175  default: {
8176  throw std::domain_error("invalid value to unflatten");
8177  }
8178  }
8179  }
8180 
8181  return *result;
8182  }

8197  reference get_unchecked(pointer ptr) const {
8198  for (const auto &reference_token : reference_tokens) {
8199  switch (ptr->m_type) {
8200  case value_t::object: {
8201  // use unchecked object access
8202  ptr = &ptr->operator[](reference_token);
8203  break;
8204  }
8205 
8206  case value_t::array: {
8207  // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
8208  if (reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0') {
8209  throw std::domain_error("array index must not begin with '0'");
8210  }
8211 
8212  if (reference_token == "-") {
8213  // explicityly treat "-" as index beyond the end
8214  ptr = &ptr->operator[](ptr->m_value.array->size());
8215  }
8216  else {
8217  // convert array index to number; unchecked access
8218  ptr = &ptr->operator[](static_cast<size_type>(std::stoi(reference_token)));
8219  }
8220  break;
8221  }
8222 
8223  default: {
8224  throw std::out_of_range("unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'");
8225  }
8226  }
8227  }
8228 
8229  return *ptr;
8230  }

8234  switch (ptr->m_type) {

8237  ptr = &ptr->at(reference_token);
8238  break;
8239  }
8240 
8241  case value_t::array: {

8243  // "-" always fails the range check
8244  throw std::out_of_range("array index '-' (" +
8245  std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()) +

8247  }
8248 
8249  // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)

8252  }

8256  break;
8257  }
8258

8260  throw std::out_of_range("unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'");
8261  }
8262  }

8349  static std::vector<std::string> split(std::string reference_string) {
8350  std::vector<std::string> result;
8351 
8352  // special case: empty reference string -> no reference tokens
8353  if (reference_string.empty()) {
8354  return result;
8355  }
8356 
8357  // check if nonempty reference string begins with slash
8358  if (reference_string[0] != '/') {
8359  throw std::domain_error("JSON pointer must be empty or begin with '/'");
8360  }
8361 
8362  // extract the reference tokens:
8363  // - slash: position of the last read slash (or end of string)
8364  // - start: position after the previous slash
8365  for (
8366  // search for the first slash after the first character
8367  size_t slash = reference_string.find_first_of("/", 1),
8368  // set the beginning of the first reference token
8369  start = 1;
8370  // we can stop if start == string::npos+1 = 0
8371  start != 0;
8372  // set the beginning of the next reference token
8373  // (will eventually be 0 if slash == std::string::npos)
8374  start = slash + 1,
8375  // find next slash
8376  slash = reference_string.find_first_of("/", start)) {
8377  // use the text between the beginning of the reference token
8378  // (start) and the last slash (slash).
8379  auto reference_token = reference_string.substr(start, slash - start);
8380 
8381  // check reference tokens are properly escaped
8382  for (size_t pos = reference_token.find_first_of("~");
8383  pos != std::string::npos;
8384  pos = reference_token.find_first_of("~", pos + 1)) {
8385  assert(reference_token[pos] == '~');
8386 
8387  // ~ must be followed by 0 or 1
8388  if (pos == reference_token.size() - 1 or
8389  (reference_token[pos + 1] != '0' and
8390  reference_token[pos + 1] != '1')) {
8391  throw std::domain_error("escape error: '~' must be followed with '0' or '1'");
8392  }
8393  }
8394 
8395  // finally, store the reference token
8396  unescape(reference_token);
8397  result.push_back(reference_token);
8398  }
8399 
8400  return result;
8401  }
8402 
8403  private:
8418  static void replace_substring(std::string &s,
8419  const std::string &f,
8420  const std::string &t) {
8421  assert(not f.empty());
8422 
8423  for (
8424  size_t pos = s.find(f); // find first occurrence of f
8425  pos != std::string::npos; // make sure f was found
8426  s.replace(pos, f.size(), t), // replace with t
8427  pos = s.find(f, pos + t.size()) // find next occurrence of f
8428  );
8429  }
8430 
8432  static std::string escape(std::string s) {
8433  // escape "~"" to "~0" and "/" to "~1"
8434  replace_substring(s, "~", "~0");
8435  replace_substring(s, "/", "~1");
8436  return s;
8437  }
8438 
8440  static void unescape(std::string &s) {
8441  // first transform any occurrence of the sequence '~1' to '/'
8442  replace_substring(s, "~1", "/");
8443  // then transform any occurrence of the sequence '~0' to '~'
8444  replace_substring(s, "~0", "~");
8445  }

8454  static void flatten(const std::string &reference_string,
8455  const basic_json &value,
8456  basic_json &result) {
8457  switch (value.m_type) {
8458  case value_t::array: {
8459  if (value.m_value.array->empty()) {
8460  // flatten empty array as null
8461  result[reference_string] = nullptr;
8462  }
8463  else {
8464  // iterate array and use index as reference string
8465  for (size_t i = 0; i < value.m_value.array->size(); ++i) {
8466  flatten(reference_string + "/" + std::to_string(i),
8467  value.m_value.array->operator[](i), result);
8468  }
8469  }
8470  break;
8471  }
8472 
8473  case value_t::object: {
8474  if (value.m_value.object->empty()) {
8475  // flatten empty object as null
8476  result[reference_string] = nullptr;
8477  }
8478  else {
8479  // iterate object and use keys as reference string
8480  for (const auto &element : *value.m_value.object) {
8481  flatten(reference_string + "/" + escape(element.first),
8482  element.second, result);
8483  }
8484  }
8485  break;
8486  }
8487 
8488  default: {
8489  // add primitive value with its reference string
8490  result[reference_string] = value;
8491  break;
8492  }
8493  }
8494  }

8501  static basic_json unflatten(const basic_json &value) {
8502  if (not value.is_object()) {
8503  throw std::domain_error("only objects can be unflattened");
8504  }
8505 
8506  basic_json result;
8507 
8508  // iterate the JSON object values
8509  for (const auto &element : *value.m_value.object) {
8510  if (not element.second.is_primitive()) {
8511  throw std::domain_error("values in object must be primitive");
8512  }
8513 
8514  // assign value to reference pointed to by JSON pointer; Note
8515  // that if the JSON pointer is "" (i.e., points to the whole
8516  // value), function get_and_create returns a reference to
8517  // result itself. An assignment will then create a primitive
8518  // value.
8519  json_pointer(element.first).get_and_create(result) = element.second;
8520  }
8521 
8522  return result;
8523  }

8710  // JSON Patch functions //
8712 
8715 
8752  basic_json patch(const basic_json &json_patch) const {
8753  // make a working copy to apply the patch to
8754  basic_json result = *this;
8755 
8756  // the valid JSON Patch operations
8757  enum class patch_operations { add, remove, replace, move, copy, test, invalid };
8758 
8759  const auto get_op = [](const std::string op) {
8760  if (op == "add") {
8761  return patch_operations::add;
8762  }
8763  if (op == "remove") {
8764  return patch_operations::remove;
8765  }
8766  if (op == "replace") {
8767  return patch_operations::replace;
8768  }
8769  if (op == "move") {
8770  return patch_operations::move;
8771  }
8772  if (op == "copy") {
8773  return patch_operations::copy;
8774  }
8775  if (op == "test") {
8776  return patch_operations::test;
8777  }
8778 
8779  return patch_operations::invalid;
8780  };
8781 
8782  // wrapper for "add" operation; add value at ptr
8783  const auto operation_add = [&result](json_pointer &ptr, basic_json val) {
8784  // adding to the root of the target document means replacing it
8785  if (ptr.is_root()) {
8786  result = val;
8787  }
8788  else {
8789  // make sure the top element of the pointer exists
8790  json_pointer top_pointer = ptr.top();
8791  if (top_pointer != ptr) {
8792  basic_json &x = result.at(top_pointer);
8793  }
8794 
8795  // get reference to parent of JSON pointer ptr
8796  const auto last_path = ptr.pop_back();
8797  basic_json &parent = result[ptr];
8798 
8799  switch (parent.m_type) {
8800  case value_t::null:
8801  case value_t::object: {
8802  // use operator[] to add value
8803  parent[last_path] = val;
8804  break;
8805  }
8806 
8807  case value_t::array: {
8808  if (last_path == "-") {
8809  // special case: append to back
8810  parent.push_back(val);
8811  }
8812  else {
8813  const auto idx = std::stoi(last_path);
8814  if (static_cast<size_type>(idx) > parent.size()) {
8815  // avoid undefined behavior
8816  throw std::out_of_range("array index " + std::to_string(idx) + " is out of range");
8817  }
8818  else {
8819  // default case: insert add offset
8820  parent.insert(parent.begin() + static_cast<difference_type>(idx), val);
8821  }
8822  }
8823  break;
8824  }
8825 
8826  default: {
8827  // if there exists a parent it cannot be primitive
8828  assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
8829  }
8830  }
8831  }
8832  };
8833 
8834  // wrapper for "remove" operation; remove value at ptr
8835  const auto operation_remove = [&result](json_pointer &ptr) {
8836  // get reference to parent of JSON pointer ptr
8837  const auto last_path = ptr.pop_back();
8838  basic_json &parent = result.at(ptr);
8839 
8840  // remove child
8841  if (parent.is_object()) {
8842  // perform range check
8843  auto it = parent.find(last_path);
8844  if (it != parent.end()) {
8845  parent.erase(it);
8846  }
8847  else {
8848  throw std::out_of_range("key '" + last_path + "' not found");
8849  }
8850  }
8851  else if (parent.is_array()) {
8852  // note erase performs range check
8853  parent.erase(static_cast<size_type>(std::stoi(last_path)));
8854  }
8855  };
8856 
8857  // type check
8858  if (not json_patch.is_array()) {
8859  // a JSON patch must be an array of objects
8860  throw std::invalid_argument("JSON patch must be an array of objects");
8861  }
8862 
8863  // iterate and apply th eoperations
8864  for (const auto &val : json_patch) {
8865  // wrapper to get a value for an operation
8866  const auto get_value = [&val](const std::string &op,
8867  const std::string &member,
8868  bool string_type) -> basic_json & {
8869  // find value
8870  auto it = val.m_value.object->find(member);
8871 
8872  // context-sensitive error message
8873  const auto error_msg = (op == "op") ? "operation" : "operation '" + op + "'";
8874 
8875  // check if desired value is present
8876  if (it == val.m_value.object->end()) {
8877  throw std::invalid_argument(error_msg + " must have member '" + member + "'");
8878  }
8879 
8880  // check if result is of type string
8881  if (string_type and not it->second.is_string()) {
8882  throw std::invalid_argument(error_msg + " must have string member '" + member + "'");
8883  }
8884 
8885  // no error: return value
8886  return it->second;
8887  };
8888 
8889  // type check
8890  if (not val.is_object()) {
8891  throw std::invalid_argument("JSON patch must be an array of objects");
8892  }
8893 
8894  // collect mandatory members
8895  const std::string op = get_value("op", "op", true);
8896  const std::string path = get_value(op, "path", true);
8897  json_pointer ptr(path);
8898 
8899  switch (get_op(op)) {
8900  case patch_operations::add: {
8901  operation_add(ptr, get_value("add", "value", false));
8902  break;
8903  }
8904 
8905  case patch_operations::remove: {
8906  operation_remove(ptr);
8907  break;
8908  }
8909 
8910  case patch_operations::replace: {
8911  // the "path" location must exist - use at()
8912  result.at(ptr) = get_value("replace", "value", false);
8913  break;
8914  }
8915 
8916  case patch_operations::move: {
8917  const std::string from_path = get_value("move", "from", true);
8918  json_pointer from_ptr(from_path);
8919 
8920  // the "from" location must exist - use at()
8921  basic_json v = result.at(from_ptr);
8922 
8923  // The move operation is functionally identical to a
8924  // "remove" operation on the "from" location, followed
8925  // immediately by an "add" operation at the target
8926  // location with the value that was just removed.
8927  operation_remove(from_ptr);
8928  operation_add(ptr, v);
8929  break;
8930  }
8931 
8932  case patch_operations::copy: {
8933  const std::string from_path = get_value("copy", "from", true);;
8934  const json_pointer from_ptr(from_path);
8935 
8936  // the "from" location must exist - use at()
8937  result[ptr] = result.at(from_ptr);
8938  break;
8939  }
8940 
8941  case patch_operations::test: {
8942  bool success = false;
8943  try {
8944  // check if "value" matches the one at "path"
8945  // the "path" location must exist - use at()
8946  success = (result.at(ptr) == get_value("test", "value", false));
8947  }
8948  catch (std::out_of_range &) {
8949  // ignore out of range errors: success remains false
8950  }
8951 
8952  // throw an exception if test fails
8953  if (not success) {
8954  throw std::domain_error("unsuccessful: " + val.dump());
8955  }
8956 
8957  break;
8958  }
8959 
8960  case patch_operations::invalid: {
8961  // op must be "add", "remove", "replace", "move", "copy", or
8962  // "test"
8963  throw std::invalid_argument("operation value '" + op + "' is invalid");
8964  }
8965  }
8966  }
8967 
8968  return result;
8969  }
8970 
9003  static basic_json diff(const basic_json &source,
9004  const basic_json &target,
9005  std::string path = "") {
9006  // the patch
9007  basic_json result(value_t::array);
9008 
9009  // if the values are the same, return empty patch
9010  if (source == target) {
9011  return result;
9012  }
9013 
9014  if (source.type() != target.type()) {
9015  // different types: replace value
9016  result.push_back(
9017  {
9018  {"op", "replace"},
9019  {"path", path},
9020  {"value", target}
9021  });
9022  }
9023  else {
9024  switch (source.type()) {
9025  case value_t::array: {
9026  // first pass: traverse common elements
9027  size_t i = 0;
9028  while (i < source.size() and i < target.size()) {
9029  // recursive call to compare array values at index i
9030  auto temp_diff = diff(source[i], target[i], path + "/" + std::to_string(i));
9031  result.insert(result.end(), temp_diff.begin(), temp_diff.end());
9032  ++i;
9033  }
9034 
9035  // i now reached the end of at least one array
9036  // in a second pass, traverse the remaining elements
9037 
9038  // remove my remaining elements
9039  while (i < source.size()) {
9040  result.push_back(object(
9041  {
9042  {"op", "remove"},
9043  {"path", path + "/" + std::to_string(i)}
9044  }));
9045  ++i;
9046  }
9047 
9048  // add other remaining elements
9049  while (i < target.size()) {
9050  result.push_back(
9051  {
9052  {"op", "add"},
9053  {"path", path + "/" + std::to_string(i)},
9054  {"value", target[i]}
9055  });
9056  ++i;
9057  }
9058 
9059  break;
9060  }
9061 
9062  case value_t::object: {
9063  // first pass: traverse this object's elements
9064  for (auto it = source.begin(); it != source.end(); ++it) {
9065  // escape the key name to be used in a JSON patch
9066  const auto key = json_pointer::escape(it.key());
9067 
9068  if (target.find(it.key()) != target.end()) {
9069  // recursive call to compare object values at key it
9070  auto temp_diff = diff(it.value(), target[it.key()], path + "/" + key);
9071  result.insert(result.end(), temp_diff.begin(), temp_diff.end());
9072  }
9073  else {
9074  // found a key that is not in o -> remove it
9075  result.push_back(object(
9076  {
9077  {"op", "remove"},
9078  {"path", path + "/" + key}
9079  }));
9080  }
9081  }
9082 
9083  // second pass: traverse other object's elements
9084  for (auto it = target.begin(); it != target.end(); ++it) {
9085  if (source.find(it.key()) == source.end()) {
9086  // found a key that is not in this -> add it
9087  const auto key = json_pointer::escape(it.key());
9088  result.push_back(
9089  {
9090  {"op", "add"},
9091  {"path", path + "/" + key},
9092  {"value", it.value()}
9093  });
9094  }
9095  }
9096 
9097  break;
9098  }
9099 
9100  default: {
9101  // both primitive type: replace value
9102  result.push_back(
9103  {
9104  {"op", "replace"},
9105  {"path", path},
9106  {"value", target}
9107  });
9108  break;
9109  }
9110  }
9111  }
9112 
9113  return result;
9114  }
9115 
9117 };
